ments to questions about campus policies, etc.  Students who wish to report a complaint or concern are encouraged to complete the Student Assistance Request .       Register a Campus Demonstration   For students who are interested in demonstrating on campus, you must register your event with the Office of the Dean of Students. Please schedule an appointment with the Dean of Students in SSB 3030 and arrive approximately 15 minutes early to fill out the necessary forms to complete registration requirements. For more information regarding UIC policy on Open Expression, please visit the link here .       Other Concerns        User icon        Academic Concerns        Flag icon         Report Sexual Misconduct        Flag icon         Report Discrimination or Harassment             Assistance    Back to main content           Academic Concerns     Academic Resources    Academic Grievances    Withdrawal    Emergencies and Absences      Health & Personal Concerns     Hospitalization & Emergencies    Mental Health    Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns    Housing Instability & Food Insecurity    Financial Concerns    Cannabis: Know the Facts      Campus Life    Faculty & Staff Resources     The Student Response Team    Behavioral Response Intervention Team      U & I Care     Meet Our Partners    Care Facts    News & Events    U & I Care Fund    U & I Care Plan                    UIC Logo        Office of the Dean of Students         DOS Offices    Career Services    Student Employment    Counseling Center    Wellness Center      For Employees    SA Human Resources    SA Technology    Leave Management    The Pulse      Safety    UIC Police    Office of Access & Equity    Contact-US    Giving         Contact   1200 West Harrison St., 3030 SSB Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-4857  dos@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Op